Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic self-assembly, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of the Tile Assembly Model and the concept of intrinsic universality suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. The lower bound on simulation power and the comparison between noncooperative and cooperative binding may involve computational complexity, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another likely sub-category. The use of tile assembly systems and the simulation of Turing machines suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the mention of three-dimensional systems and the comparison between two- and three-dimensional simulations suggest that the paper may involve computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category as well.
